What happens in the shrine remains in the shrine What happened in the shrine is no longer a secret as Femi Kuti lives up to his father’s legacy of being outspoken. He made a revelation to President Emmanuel Macron that the road leading to the shrine was fixed because of his visit. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-684336 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Femi-Kuti-and-Emmanuel-Macron.png" alt="" width="900" height="315" /> <img class="aligncenter wp-image-684340 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Femi-Kuti-Replies-Fan-1.png" alt="" width="900" height="192" /> Femi Kuti inherited the shrine from his father Fela Kuti, the Afrobeat Legend who was known for his bluntness in criticizing the government. According to Femi Kuti’s Instagram page, he had other discussions with President Macron on Migrants and the future of the youth.